definitions.definition: ( heraldry ) A twist of cloth or wreath, typically placed underneath and forming part of a crest (as an orle or wreath ) and customarily shown with six twists, the first tincture being the tincture of the field , the second the tincture of the metal, and so on; rarely, it occurs as a charge.
